{"word":"ἀνεγείρω","slug":"ἀνεγείρω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνεγείρω</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to wake up, rouse</i>, <el>ἐξ ὕπνου, ἐκ λεχέων</el> <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> <i>to wake up, raise</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> also <i>to rouse, encourage</i>, <b><a href='S:Odyssey'>Od.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of buildings, <i>to raise</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}